pa911_description: Comprehensive annual exam including physical exam and preventative health review.
Core vaccinations and booster shots as recommended for the pet’s age and species.
Extended first-time visit to review history, perform exam, and create care plan.
Problem-focused exam for illness, injury, or new symptoms.
Routine dental cleaning under anesthesia (pre-op exam required).
Bath, nail trim, ear cleaning, and brush-out (dogs and cats only).
Pre-surgical consultation to review options, risks, and recovery expectations.
Consultation for behavior issues and training recommendations.
